3#ifndef __NVKM_GRCTX_H__
4#define __NVKM_GRCTX_H__
5#include <core/gpuobj.h>
6
7struct nvkm_grctx {
8 struct nvkm_device *device;
9
10 enum {
11 NVKM_GRCTX_PROG,
12 NVKM_GRCTX_VALS
13 } mode;
14 u32 *ucode;
15 struct nvkm_gpuobj *data;
16
17 u32 ctxprog_max;
18 u32 ctxprog_len;
19 u32 ctxprog_reg;
20 int ctxprog_label[32];
21 u32 ctxvals_pos;
22 u32 ctxvals_base;
23};
24
25static inline void
26cp_out(struct nvkm_grctx *ctx, u32 inst)
27{
28 u32 *ctxprog = ctx->ucode;
29
30 if (ctx->mode != NVKM_GRCTX_PROG)
31 return;
32
33 BUG_ON(ctx->ctxprog_len == ctx->ctxprog_max);
34 ctxprog[ctx->ctxprog_len++] = inst;
35}
36
37static inline void
38cp_lsr(struct nvkm_grctx *ctx, u32 val)
39{
40 cp_out(ctx, CP_LOAD_SR | val);
41}
42
43static inline void
44cp_ctx(struct nvkm_grctx *ctx, u32 reg, u32 length)
45{
46 ctx->ctxprog_reg = (reg - 0x00400000) >> 2;
47
48 ctx->ctxvals_base = ctx->ctxvals_pos;
49 ctx->ctxvals_pos = ctx->ctxvals_base + length;
50
51 if (length > (CP_CTX_COUNT >> CP_CTX_COUNT_SHIFT)) {
52 cp_lsr(ctx, length);
53 length = 0;
54 }
55
56 cp_out(ctx, CP_CTX | (length << CP_CTX_COUNT_SHIFT) | ctx->ctxprog_reg);
57}
58
59static inline void
60cp_name(struct nvkm_grctx *ctx, int name)
61{
62 u32 *ctxprog = ctx->ucode;
63 int i;
64
65 if (ctx->mode != NVKM_GRCTX_PROG)
66 return;
67
68 ctx->ctxprog_label[name] = ctx->ctxprog_len;
69 for (i = 0; i < ctx->ctxprog_len; i++) {
70 if ((ctxprog[i] & 0xfff00000) != 0xff400000)
71 continue;
72 if ((ctxprog[i] & CP_BRA_IP) != ((name) << CP_BRA_IP_SHIFT))
73 continue;
74 ctxprog[i] = (ctxprog[i] & 0x00ff00ff) |
75 (ctx->ctxprog_len << CP_BRA_IP_SHIFT);
76 }
77}
78
79static inline void
80_cp_bra(struct nvkm_grctx *ctx, u32 mod, int flag, int state, int name)
81{
82 int ip = 0;
83
84 if (mod != 2) {
85 ip = ctx->ctxprog_label[name] << CP_BRA_IP_SHIFT;
86 if (ip == 0)
87 ip = 0xff000000 | (name << CP_BRA_IP_SHIFT);
88 }
89
90 cp_out(ctx, CP_BRA | (mod << 18) | ip | flag |
91 (state ? 0 : CP_BRA_IF_CLEAR));
92}
93#define cp_bra(c, f, s, n) _cp_bra((c), 0, CP_FLAG_##f, CP_FLAG_##f##_##s, n)
94#define cp_cal(c, f, s, n) _cp_bra((c), 1, CP_FLAG_##f, CP_FLAG_##f##_##s, n)
95#define cp_ret(c, f, s) _cp_bra((c), 2, CP_FLAG_##f, CP_FLAG_##f##_##s, 0)
96
97static inline void
98_cp_wait(struct nvkm_grctx *ctx, int flag, int state)
99{
100 cp_out(ctx, CP_WAIT | flag | (state ? CP_WAIT_SET : 0));
101}
102#define cp_wait(c, f, s) _cp_wait((c), CP_FLAG_##f, CP_FLAG_##f##_##s)
103
104static inline void
105_cp_set(struct nvkm_grctx *ctx, int flag, int state)
106{
107 cp_out(ctx, CP_SET | flag | (state ? CP_SET_1 : 0));
108}
109#define cp_set(c, f, s) _cp_set((c), CP_FLAG_##f, CP_FLAG_##f##_##s)
110
111static inline void
112cp_pos(struct nvkm_grctx *ctx, int offset)
113{
114 ctx->ctxvals_pos = offset;
115 ctx->ctxvals_base = ctx->ctxvals_pos;
116
117 cp_lsr(ctx, ctx->ctxvals_pos);
118 cp_out(ctx, CP_SET_CONTEXT_POINTER);
119}
120
121static inline void
122gr_def(struct nvkm_grctx *ctx, u32 reg, u32 val)
123{
124 if (ctx->mode != NVKM_GRCTX_VALS)
125 return;
126
127 reg = (reg - 0x00400000) / 4;
128 reg = (reg - ctx->ctxprog_reg) + ctx->ctxvals_base;
129
130 nvkm_wo32(ctx->data, reg * 4, val);
131}
132#endif
